Date:4/25/2012 9:51:30 AM
From:Spekulatius
NikhilJog, re gold producers

<blockquote>Gold producers - THese guys get the gold@ USD 500/600 an ounce
while the metal is trading at $1600.</blockquote> The disparity between the
performance of the metal itself and the producers of gold (which is essentially
a leveraged bet on gold) are what caught the attention of value investors. So
far, the disparity only get's larger, gold itself essentially stayed put, while
the gold miners have fallen.

Gold miners have been trading at elevated valuation ratios relative to other
mining companies for a long time but that is no more.

FWIW, NEM may have other issues that have caused a revision in earning forecast
(rising costs, the Peru mine that has been delayed? )that I want to learn more
about before adding.
