From:Paul Senior
US/Canada agreement changed last year, Madharry, and with Canadian
dividend/distribution payers there is no 15% tax withheld if stock is in ira.
There is that tax withheld though if stock is in a USA taxable account.

Withholding rules and amounts vary by country. For example with French stocks,
the withholding tax is 25% if in ira, but "only" 15% if your French stock is
held in taxable account.
