Date:4/28/2012 11:36:48 PM
From:Sergio H
TTEK update.

Hit 52 wk high last week. It's still trading at very reasonable multiples.

Looking at it historically, TTEK has managed to eke out growth in earnings
averaging in the mid teens or better for at least the last five years. They
have successfully offset the decrease in U.S. govt. spending by increasing
their revenues and earnings from international sources as well as U.S.
commercial sources. The stock is up significantly this year and so is the U.S.
stock market. I think going forward TTEK is well positioned regardless of what
happens with the U.S. stock market in general.

Their website offers a wealth of information. Start with presentations found
under Investor Relations at
http://www.tetratech.com/

TTEK offers advisory services and does not have the costs associated with
delivering infrastucture services. They offer knowledge and therefore the
margins are pure profit. The need for their knowledge base is just becoming a
necessity. TTEK deals with solving water problems. People need water and they
assure that when you turn on your tap, water will come out. TTEK provides water
solutions to California, Colorado, Brazil and Afghanistan. Additionally, they
are also involved in water solutions for the mining industry. There is a good
presentation on their website on this. Mining has increased its impact on the
environment and therefore has increased the need for environment protection
services that TTEK offers.

Earnings report is coming up in the first week in May. I like this stock going
forward. Institutional investment has been solid, insider interest has been
lacking. Lots of analysts follow this stock but probably due to the heavy
competition, TTEK has not received much press.

TTEK has almost no debt, so it is in a good position to expand growth by
acquisition as it sees fit, but however management chooses to go forward, they
have established a good platform to build on.
