A few trades in the IRA account to start what I feel is a value Buy in BBEP.
According to my EK$ calculation BBEP is 15% undervalued. The EK$ fair value is
$22.10/share but their is a small EPS history especially w/ their recent
acquisitions.

BBEP owns and operates natural gas, oil and midstream assets in Michigan,
Indiana and Kentucky, including fields in the Antrim Shale in Michigan and New
Albany Shale in Indiana and Kentucky, transmission and gathering pipelines,
three gas processing plants and four NGL recovery plants. Their transmission,
gathering pipelines and NG processing plant infrastructure holds value for me
as I expect many of these smaller operations will eventually be consolidated
into larger operations.

The value lies in their pipeline easement agreements that are worth a lot more
to a very large operator especially in the regional areas BBEP operates in.

To fund the transaction I sold positions in MDU and AQUNF. MDU is selling at
their higher price range and I believe I can buy shares 20% lower. AQUNF
although a good dividend payer (4.4% yield) does not provide me the growth and
dividend potential that BBEP does. I have a 10% capital gain from my original
buys in 5/2011 which is pretty good for a water treatment utility. I still
maintain a small position in the portfolio that will allow me to track the
growth of the company.

